The paper discusses attention networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) tasks. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions deep neural networks, which fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses visual analytics, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves analyzing and understanding large amounts of data.
